workflow.name: YouTube optimization automation: Google Sheets + DeepSeek integration
workflow.description:
Unlock the full potential of your YouTube channel with our powerful integration that connects Google Sheets and DeepSeek AI ‚Äî designed to skyrocket your video visibility and engagement without manual hassle.

What this integration does for you:
Automates video data management by pulling your YouTube URLs straight from Google Sheets ‚Äî no more copy-pasting or manual tracking.

Extracts your current titles and descriptions directly from YouTube, giving you a clear starting point.

Generates 3 high-impact, SEO-optimized titles plus 1 compelling, conversion-focused description ‚Äî crafted by DeepSeek‚Äôs AI to grab attention and rank higher.

Updates your Google Sheet automatically with new optimized titles and descriptions ‚Äî keeping all your video info in one place, ready to publish.

Why it matters:
In the crowded world of YouTube, having the right title and description can make all the difference between millions of views or being lost in the noise. This integration takes the guesswork out of optimization, saving you time and boosting your channel‚Äôs growth with proven AI-driven content.

You need to Sheet with columns:

Url
Keyword
Status
Old Title
New Title
Old Description
New Description

My contact: 
jacobmarketingservice@gmail.com

parameters.text:
=You are a YouTube SEO and copywriting expert.

I will give you:
- the current (old) video title,
- the main keyword we want to rank for.

Your job is to rewrite the title to:
1. Be **more attention-grabbing** (clickable / curiosity-driven),
2. Include the **given keyword naturally** (for SEO),
3. Stay relevant to the original title's topic,
5. Use power words, numbers, questions, or hooks where possible.

Output only 3 optimized YouTube titles. Number them. Do not add anything else.

Old title: "{{ $json.title }}"
Keyword: "{{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.keyword }}"

Very important: Output only a **valid single-line JSON** with a key called `newTitle`. Do not use markdown, do not include explanations, lists, or comments.

Format example:
{"newTitle": "..."}

messageValues.message: Very important: Output only a **valid single-line JSON** with a key called `newTitle`. Do not use markdown, do not include explanations, lists, or comments.  Format example: {"newTitle": "..."}

parameters.text:
=You are an expert in YouTube SEO and copywriting.

Your task is to rewrite a YouTube video description using the following inputs:
- The **original description**
- The **main keyword** we want to rank for

Instructions:
1. Keep the original **timeline section** exactly as it is (do not change order or content).
2. Improve the rest of the description to:
   - Be more **engaging and persuasive** (increase watch time and clicks)
   - Naturally include the **given keyword** for better SEO
   - Encourage viewers to subscribe, comment, or check other content
   - Use line breaks, emojis (optionally), and formatting for readability
3. Output the final version as plain text. Do not explain anything.
4. The new description should be max 1500 characters if possible.

---

Original description:
"""
{{ $json.description }}
"""

Keyword: "{{ $('Get row(s) in sheet').item.json.keyword }}"

 Return in this JSON format:
{
  "newDescription": "..."
}
